<h2>Application Rules and Procedures </h2>
<p>
                    
                    1.) You must meet the following requirements:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Minimum level is 65.&nbsp; Rare exceptions may be made by a vote 
            of the officers for a particularly needed class</li>
            <li>Requested classes do change from time to time.  Please check any 
			recent announcements in the Application Forum for details<br>
			<u><b>Note</b></u>: If you are not one of the classes requested on the Application Forum, 
			please have your sponsor contact an officer.  Exceptions must be approved by the officers.</li>
</ul>
          <p>2.) To 
          apply - Read the
          <a href="http://www.divineprophecy.org/Info/charter.asp" target="_blank" >
          Divine Prophecy Charter</a>.&nbsp; If you are willing and able to comply 
          with all of these guidelines, post an application on the
          <a href="http://www.divineprophecy.org/forum/forum_topics.asp?FID=2" target="_blank" >
          Application Board</a>.&nbsp; You should include the following:&nbsp;</span></p>
          
          
<ol type="A">
  <li>Full Name of your Main Character&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>Class/Race/Level of your main character&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>Any alternate characters you play&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>What time zone you live in&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>Why do you want to join Divine Prophecy?&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>What are your expectations of a guild and your guildmates?&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>What other guilds have you been a member?&nbsp; Why did you leave?&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>Who is your sponsor (See Below)?&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>What are your unbuffed resistances (i.e. magic, fire, cold, etc.)?&nbsp;</span></li>
  <li>List all PoP flags and keys</li>
  <li>How many AA's do you currently have? Feel free to list any particular AA's you've finished that you feel are worthy of mention.</li>
  <li>Was this character originally created and leveled by you?  If not, at what level did you get the character and how long have you had it?</li>
</ol>
</p>
          <p>3.) 
          All applicants must have a sponsor within Divine 
          Prophecy prior to applying.&nbsp; This sponsor must be a full member (no probationary 
          members) in good standing.&nbsp; To find a sponsor, we suggest that you 
          group with
          <a target="_blank"  href="../scripts/roster.asp">our members</a> 
			whenever possible and get to know them.&nbsp; Once you have 
			developed a relationship with them, approach them about sponsorship.&nbsp; 
			Your sponsor must post their willingness to support you on your 
			application.</span></p>
          <p>4.) 
          After your sponsor has agreed to support you formally on the
          <a href="http://www.divineprophecy.org/forum/forum_topics.asp?FID=2" target="_blank" >
          Application board</a>, there will be a one-week incubation period 
          before you are invited to DP as a probationary member. </span></p>
          <ul>
            <li>
            <p style="margin-right: 0in; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 12.0pt">
Please note that applications can be canceled by a majority 
            vote by the Officers</span></li>
            <li>
            <p style="margin-right: 0in; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 12.0pt">
            
Probation will last for 30 days and 4 full guild raids.&nbsp; It will be 
            your responsibility to attend the 4 raids based on posted raids on 
            the Raid Board, which you will be given access to upon being 
            invited.&nbsp; Probation will not expire until you have attended 4 raids 
            (so, if you do not attend 4 raids in 30 days, your probation will be 
            extended). </span></li>
            <li>
            <p style="margin-right: 0in; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 12.0pt">
            
During the probation period, the ability to roll on any raid drops 
            will not be available unless no full member will use such drops 
            (this is at the discretion of the Raid Leader).&nbsp; Further, 
            &quot;hand-me-downs,&quot; discounts, donations, loans, and other similar 
            requests should not be solicited from the guild until probation is 
            completed.</span></li>
            <li>
			<p style="margin-right: 0in; margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 12.0pt">At any time during the application or probation 
            period, the consideration of an individual maybe declined should the 
            minimum of five full DP members express an objection of membership.&nbsp; These objections will then be shared only with the 
            other officers to verify and void applications or promotions.</span>&nbsp; 
            Additionally, you must have received at least ten approvals from the 
            membership.&nbsp; The probation period will be extended until either 
            ten approvals or five disapprovals have been met.</li>
          </ul>
          <p>5.) 
          Your sponsor is responsible for your actions during this time.&nbsp; You 
          should check with him/her in case there are any doubts on what is 
          appropriate or inappropriate behavior.</span></p>
          <p>6.) 
          Upon completion of the probationary requirements, your sponsor must 
          formally post on the Application Board their support or lack there of 
          in your full membership.&nbsp; At this time, the officers will also discuss 
          your membership.&nbsp; Any reservations or concerns will result in us not 
          offering you a full membership in Divine Prophecy.</span></p>
          <p>7.) In the unfortunate 
          situation where a sponsor of a probate leaves the guild, the probate 
          will need to find a new sponsor from within the guild.&nbsp;
          <span style="color: black">If a 
          probate is without sponsor for more than&nbsp;five days, then they will 
          need to reapply and begin the process over again.&nbsp; If&nbsp;the 
          probate&nbsp;obtains a new sponsor within that time,&nbsp;their previous time 
          spent in&nbsp;prior probate status will be credited toward completion less 
          the time spent without a sponsor.</span></p>
          <p><b><u><span style="color: black">
          Additional Comments:</span></u></b></p>
          <p>- 
          Divine Prophecy raids on a regular basis.&nbsp; Member participation in 
          these raids is necessary for the furthering of our guild.&nbsp; If you do 
          not plan to attend regularly, do not apply.</span></p>
          <p>- As 
          DP is a raiding guild, you should own resistance gear.&nbsp; It is strongly 
          recommended that your unbuffed fire, cold and magic resist are over 
          100 (this means with you and your gear only, no self or group buffs or 
          songs).</span></p>
          <p>- We 
          do not support guild shopping.&nbsp; If you are applying to many guilds on 
          Xev, do not bother posting here.&nbsp; Any applications to other guilds 
          will result in the end of your trial probationary period or the 
          invalidation of your application.&nbsp; In addition, if you are currently 
          guilded, we will not consider your application.</span></p>
          <p>- Divine Prophecy will not assist with any epic mobs until sixty 
          days (60) after invite.&nbsp; At this point, the officer in charge of epics 
          will prioritize any assistance based on the benefit of the guild at 
          her discretion.</p>
          <p>- If denied membership during either the application or probation 
          phases, you will be allowed to re-apply in three months after your 
          initial application, and you will only be allowed to re-apply once. If 
          denied a second time, there will be no further chances.</p>
<p>- Real Life (RL) friends may be admitted under the family application rules, 
except as follows:</p>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - The applicant must be sponsored through the normal 
process<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - The applicant must a minimum of level 65<br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - The applicant must note on their application that they are 
friends of a nonprobationary member</p>
